  "prompt": "What is the chemical formula for zinc? How is this determined?",
  "response": "The chemical formula for zinc is simply \"Zn.\" This formula is determined based on zinc's status as a pure chemical element. In the periodic table, each element is represented by a unique symbol, which generally originates from the element's English name or its Latin name. For zinc, the symbol \"Zn\" comes from its English name.\n\nUnlike compounds that are composed of two or more elements and require specific formulas to indicate the proportions and types of atoms involved, single-element formulas consist solely of the element's symbol. Therefore, the chemical formula for zinc, indicating it is an individual element, is \"Zn.\"",
